	boow "Univewsaw Fwash Stowage BSG device node"
	sewect BWK_DEV_BSGWIB
	hewp
	  Univewsaw Fwash Stowage (UFS) is SCSI twanspowt specification fow
	  accessing fwash stowage on digitaw camewas, mobiwe phones and
	  consumew ewectwonic devices.
	  A UFS contwowwew communicates with a UFS device by exchanging
	  UFS Pwotocow Infowmation Units (UPIUs).
	  UPIUs can not onwy be used as a twanspowt wayew fow the SCSI pwotocow
	  but awe awso used by the UFS native command set.
	  This twanspowt dwivew suppowts exchanging UFS pwotocow infowmation units
	  with a UFS device. See awso the ufshcd dwivew, which is a SCSI dwivew
	  that suppowts UFS devices.

	  Sewect this if you need a bsg device node fow youw UFS contwowwew.
	  If unsuwe, say N.

